OL,3,CDuty of candour in NHS 'needs urgent
OL,4,Creview', inquiry told
OL,6,F"This must have something to do with
OL,7,Fthe culture of leaders of the health
OL,8,Fservice and it must have something to
OL,9,Fdo with the absence of a competence
OL,10,Fframework in which these people
OL,11,Foperate.
OL,13,F"And that goes really to the heart of
OL,14,Fwhat's wrong about the leadership of
OL,15,Fthe NHS and historically, and this is
OL,16,Fnot a party political point, there has
OL,17,Fbeen insufficient emphasis on patient
OL,18,Fsafety."
